AB  - In a past issue of this journal, Carl J. Norstrøm [3] developed a sufficiency condition for the existence of a unique nonnegative internal rate of return for an investment project. His method is appealing because it involves a simple computation using cumulative undiscounted cash flows and because it applies to a wide range of practical situations.
